<Feedforward Candidate Generator Summary: bin>
- Purpose: generate two binning-focused feedforward candidates from InputData.
- Output format: valid JSON object only, no extra text.

Core expectations:
- Use embodiment cues first: spatialContextTypes, then gaze/head context.
- If deictic speech appears and gaze target exists, center binning around nearby gaze datapoints.
- Produce c1 and c2 with required cluster metadata from InputData.
- Fill only bin-related decision fields and keep schema paths unchanged.
- Prefer non-repetitive bin settings and avoid reusing previous axis-range patterns.

Binning guidance:
- Support AxisBin, AttributeBin, or CustomBoundary.
- Use numeric edges or steps; avoid hybrid string ranges.
- Keep insights action-oriented with a separate effect sentence.
- Ground insights in concrete values and spatial viewpoint context.

Public-release note:
- Detailed policy rules and long examples are omitted in this public release.
</Feedforward Candidate Generator Summary: bin>
